The paper focuses on learning a contextualized sparse representation for open-domain question answering, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also utilizes machine learning techniques, such as self-attention and kernelization, which are common in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the application of the proposed model to image-based question answering, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
